<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the original description some of the 
<typeStatus box="[919,1017,296,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">syntypes</typeStatus>
are males. Since no male could be located it can be stated with certainty that some of the specimens (
<typeStatus box="[950,1116,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
) remain undiscovered. The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[305,449,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Poeantius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollis">
<emphasis box="[305,449,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">P. brevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[504,619,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Poeantius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis box="[504,619,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">P. lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[772,934,367,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" refString="Distant, W. L. (1910) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota - Vol. V. Heteroptera: Appendix. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, xii + 362 pp." type="book" year="1910">
Distant (
<number box="[868,926,368,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
is hereby confirmed.
</paragraph>
